    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While it's natural to desire a more immediate solution, abruptly stopping sertraline or starting a new supplement like St John's wort without professional guidance can be risky. Healthcare professionals can provide personalized advice based on your specific health situation and help you manage side effects safely and effectively.\n\nSuddenly switching over to St John's wort might not provide results comparable to sertraline and can have unintended interactions with other medications you may be taking. The best course of action is to discuss your symptoms and concerns with your healthcare provider, who can help you find a approach that considers both your mental health needs and quality of life. It may still take some time to make an appointment, but your health and safety are worth it.\n\nIf your nausea remains intolerable, your doctor may be able to provide an alternative treatment plan or adjust your dosage to minimize side effects. It’s important to never self-adjust medications, as it might lead to harmful consequences. Barriers such as disorganization or time constraints can increase stress, avoidable with a little effort and planning. Make the effort to safeguard your health.",
